.TH AURA 1 "2026-04-16" "Aura 0.1.0" "Aura Manual"
.SH NAME
aura \- autonomous assistant on BEAM that orchestrates work through persistent
flares, scheduled tasks, and domain\-partitioned knowledge
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gleam run \-\- start
.br
.B gleam run \-\- init
.br
.B bash scripts/deploy.sh
.SH DESCRIPTION
Aura is an OTP application.
Every component is a supervised actor.
The brain receives Discord messages, routes them to domains, runs an LLM tool
loop, and dispatches flares for work that requires a coding agent.
Memory, state, and conversation history persist across restarts via SQLite and
structured markdown files.
.PP
Aura runs on Eisenhower (192.168.50.140) as a launchd service
.RB ( com.aura.agent ).
It communicates via Discord.
.SS Supervision tree
.nf
supervisor (OneForOne)
\(lq\(rq\(rq db               SQLite actor \(em serialized reads/writes
\(lq\(rq\(rq poller           Discord gateway WebSocket
\(lq\(rq\(rq flare_manager    Flare lifecycle \(em roster, dispatch, monitor, persist
\(lq\(rq\(rq brain            Message routing, LLM tool loop, streaming, handback
\(lq\(rq\(rq scheduler        Config\-driven cron + interval schedules
.fi
.PP
All actors restart independently.
A crash in one does not affect the others.
.SS Subsystems
.TP
.B Flares
Persistent coding agent sessions dispatched to do work.
See
.BR aura\-flares (7).
.TP
.B Domains
Knowledge partitions \(em isolated config, memory, state, and Discord channel
per area of work.
Domains are context selectors, not capability boundaries.
All tools are available in all channels.
.TP
.B Memory
Three keyed\-entry targets: state (per\-domain status), memory (per\-domain
knowledge), user (global profile).
Only the brain writes memory; flares report back.
Active review every 10 turns auto\-persists observations.
.TP
.B Conversations
Per\-channel message history.
In\-memory buffer backed by SQLite.
Tiered auto\-compression: tool pruning at 50%, LLM summarization at 70% of
context window.
.TP
.B Skills
Directory with SKILL.md and optional CLI entrypoint.
Instruction\-only skills teach the LLM; external skills run as subprocesses.
.TP
.B Schedules
Config\-driven periodic tasks in schedules.toml.
Supports fixed intervals ("15m") and cron expressions ("0 9 * * *").
.TP
.B Vision
Two\-model pipeline: vision model describes images, orchestrator runs tool loop
with enriched message.
.TP
.B Shell
General\-purpose shell execution with layered security.
41 dangerous command patterns, approval flow via Discord buttons.
See
.BR aura\-diagnostics (7).
.SH LIMITATIONS
.IP \(bu 2
Stdio ACP sessions die on deploy.
Conversation preserved via \-\-resume but in\-flight work is lost.
.IP \(bu 2
No graceful shutdown \(em process stops on SIGTERM.
SQLite WAL handles crash recovery.
.IP \(bu 2
Brain is single\-threaded \(em one message at a time.
Flares run in parallel but handback processing is sequential.
.IP \(bu 2
Streaming tool call parsing is manual JSON extraction \(em fragile for
non\-standard APIs.
.IP \(bu 2
Discord only \(em Telegram/Slack gateway modules not yet built (schema ready).
.IP \(bu 2
claude\-agent\-acp does not support CLI permission flags.
Permissions must be configured via ~/.claude/settings.json.
.IP \(bu 2
Orphan claude\-agent\-acp processes accumulate.
No automated cleanup.
